The paper discusses learning latent variable models through tensor methods, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on overcomplete models, where the dimensionality of the latent space exceeds the observed dimensionality. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the most likely category. 

The paper also discusses concentration bounds and sample complexity, which are topics that are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and statistical learning (cs.ST). Additionally, the paper considers models such as multiview mixtures and sparse coding, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, the paper could also be categorized under these sub-categories, in decreasing order of likelihood.
